Field_Binary.name: control_auth_id
Field_Binary.description: Control authority identifier. ; NJPL indicates that the data description information for this SFDU is maintained and disseminated by NASA/JPL.

Field_Binary.name: sfdu_version_id
Field_Binary.description: SFDU label version ID.; 2 indicates that the length attribute field in bytes 12 to 19 is formatted as a binary unsigned integer.

Field_Binary.name: sfdu_class_id
Field_Binary.description: SFDU class ID.; I indicates that this SFDU contains data to be used by an application process.

Field_Binary.name: reserve2
Field_Binary.description: Reserved.; Two bytes.

Field_Binary.name: data_description_id
Field_Binary.description: Data description identifier.; Uniquely identifies the data description information held by the control authority identified in the Control authority identifier item for this type of SFDU.; C123 => Uplink types; C124 => Downlink types; C125 => Derived types; C126 => Interferometric types; C127 => Filtered types

Field_Binary.name: sfdu_length
Field_Binary.description: Length attribute of the tracking data SFDU.; Indicates the length of the data following this element.; DT0 => 162; DT1 => 358 ; DT2 => 194 ; DT3 => 304 ; DT4 => 276 ; DT5 => 388 ; DT6 => 200; DT7 => 330; DT8 => 178 ; DT9 => 124; DT10 => 204 ; DT11 => 182; DT12 => 164 ; DT13 => 160; DT14 => 348; DT15 => 194; DT16 => 182 + 18 * num_obs; DT17 => 194 + 22 * num_obs

Field_Binary.name: chdo_type
Field_Binary.description: Type attribute of the aggregation CHDO.; A value of 1 indicates that this CHDO is an aggregation of CHDOs

Field_Binary.name: chdo_length
Field_Binary.description: Length attribute of the aggregation CHDO.; Indicates the length of the sum of the primary and secondary CHDOs.; CHDO 132 => 78; CHDO 133 => 122; CHDO 134 => 136; CHDO 135 => 100; CHDO 136 => 110

Field_Binary.name: chdo_type
Field_Binary.description: Type attribute of the primary CHDO.; A value of 2 indicates that this CHDO is a primary CHDO.

Field_Binary.name: chdo_length
Field_Binary.description: Length attribute of the primary CHDO. Indicates the length, in bytes, of the value field (bytes after this item) of the primary CHDO.

Field_Binary.name: mjr_data_class
Field_Binary.description: Major data class.; A value of 6 indicates that the data in this SFDU is ground station monitor data.

Field_Binary.name: mnr_data_class
Field_Binary.description: Minor data class.; Indicates data is processed tracking data.

Field_Binary.name: mission_id
Field_Binary.description: Mission ID.

Field_Binary.name: format_code
Field_Binary.description: Format code.; Also referred to as the data type.; 0 => Uplink Carrier Phase; 1 => Downlink Carrier Phase; 2 => Uplink Sequential Ranging Phase; 3 => Downlink Sequential Ranging Phase; 4 => Uplink PN Ranging Phase; 5 => Downlink PN Ranging Phase; 6 => Doppler; 7 => Sequential Ranging; 8 => Angles; 9 => Ramps ; 10 => VLBI; 11 => DRVID ; 12 => Smoothed Noise; 13 => Allan Deviation; 14 => PN Ranging; 15 => Tone Ranging; 16 => Carrier Observable; 17 => Total Phase Observable

Field_Binary.name: chdo_type
Field_Binary.description: Type attribute of the secondary CHDO.

Field_Binary.name: chdo_length
Field_Binary.description: Length attribute of the secondary CHDO. Indicates the length, in bytes, of the value field (bytes after this item) of the secondary CHDO.

Field_Binary.name: orig_id
Field_Binary.description: Originator ID.; Indicates where this SFDU was originated.

Field_Binary.name: last_modifier_id
Field_Binary.description: Last modifier ID.; Indicates where this SFDU was last modified.

Field_Binary.name: reserve1
Field_Binary.description: Reserved. ; For future expansion of scft_id.

Field_Binary.name: scft_id
Field_Binary.description: Spacecraft number.;

Field_Binary.name: rec_seq_num
Field_Binary.description: Record sequence number (RSN).; Begins with zero; increments by one for each successive tracking SFDU of the same type; wraps around from 232-1 to zero. Value is reset to zero when software is restarted.

Field_Binary.name: year
Field_Binary.description: Time tag year.

Field_Binary.name: doy
Field_Binary.description: Time tag day of year.

Field_Binary.name: sec
Field_Binary.description: Time tag seconds of day.

Field_Binary.name: rct_day
Field_Binary.description: Record creation time days.; Days since 1/1/1958.

Field_Binary.name: rct_msec
Field_Binary.description: Record creation time milliseconds of day.

Field_Binary.name: stn_stream_src
Field_Binary.description: Station stream source.; 1 => UPL/DTT ; 2 => non-UPL-DTT: TRK?2?30; 3 => non-UPL-DTT: TRK?2?20

Field_Binary.name: ul_band
Field_Binary.description: Uplink frequency band.; 0 => Unknown or not applicable; 1 => S-band; 2 => X-band; 3 => Ka-band; 4 => Ku-band; 5 => L-band

Field_Binary.name: ul_assembly_num
Field_Binary.description: Uplink Assembly Number. ; Note that this is to allow for potential future cases where there might be more than one uplink of the same band at the same antenna.; 0 => Unknown/Not applicable; 1 => S-/X-band uplink; 2 => Ka-band uplink

Field_Binary.name: transmit_num
Field_Binary.description: Transmitter number. ; Value depends on transmitter used. A value of 0 means that the number is unknown or not applicable.

Field_Binary.name: transmit_stat
Field_Binary.description: Transmit Status.; 0 => Not transmitting out the horn; 1 => Transmitting out the horn; 2 => Invalid or unknown

Field_Binary.name: transmit_mode
Field_Binary.description: Transmitter mode.; 0 => Low power; 1 => High power; 2 => Invalid or unknown

Field_Binary.name: cmd_modul_stat
Field_Binary.description: Command modulation status.; 0 => OFF; 1 => ON; 2 => Invalid or unknown

Field_Binary.name: rng_modul_stat
Field_Binary.description: Ranging modulation status.; 0 => OFF; 1 => ON; 2 => Invalid or unknown

Field_Binary.name: transmit_time_tag_delay
Field_Binary.description: Transmit time tag delay. ; Value used to offset uplink time tag (e.g., for Goldstone Beam Waveguide antennas). A value of -1.0 indicates invalid (or not provided).

Field_Binary.name: ul_zheight_corr
Field_Binary.description: Uplink Z-height correction.; Value of -99.0 indicates invalid.

Field_Binary.name: dl_dss_id
Field_Binary.description: Downlink antenna number.;

Field_Binary.name: reserve1a
Field_Binary.description: Reserved.; One byte.

Field_Binary.name: dl_chan_num
Field_Binary.description: Downlink channel number.; Value of 0 implies unknown.

Field_Binary.name: prdx_mode
Field_Binary.description: Predicts mode.; Predicts subset used by downlink channel.; 0 => No Predicts; 1 => One-way; 2 => Two-way; 3 => Three-way; 4 => Unknown

Field_Binary.name: ul_prdx_stn
Field_Binary.description: Uplink station used for predicts.; Valid only if prdx_mode is 2 or 3. A value of 0 means that the number is unknown or not valid (e.g., no uplink).

Field_Binary.name: ul_band_dl
Field_Binary.description: Uplink frequency band assumed by downlink.; Uplink band value used by downlink for turn around computations.; 0 => Unknown or not applicable; 1 => S-band ; 2 => X-band; 3 => Ka-band; 4 => Ku-band; 5 => L-band

Field_Binary.name: array_delay
Field_Binary.description: Array delay value. ; Time delay added to path by arraying equipment. Obtained from arraying equipment. Any measurements include this delay. Valid only if Array Flag (array_flag) is non-zero.

Field_Binary.name: fts_vld_flag
Field_Binary.description: Frequency and Timing (FTS) validity.; 0 => Equipment is not synced with FTS; 1 => Equipment is synced with FTS

Field_Binary.name: carr_lock_stat
Field_Binary.description: Carrier lock status.; 0 => Off; 1 => Open (using only predicts); 2 => Acquiring, FFT Search; 3 => Acquiring, Waiting for Lock Decision; 4 => In Lock; 5 => Out of Lock

Field_Binary.name: array_flag
Field_Binary.description: Array flag.; 0 => Non-arrayed; 1 => Arrayed with FSP #1; 2 => Arrayed with FSP #2

Field_Binary.name: lna_num
Field_Binary.description: LNA Number.; Value of 0 indicates unknown.

Field_Binary.name: rcv_time_tag_delay
Field_Binary.description: Receive time tag delay. ; Value used to offset downlink time tag (e.g., for Goldstone Beam Waveguide antennas). A value of -1.0 indicates invalid (or not provided).

Field_Binary.name: dl_zheight_corr
Field_Binary.description: Downlink Z-height correction.; Value of -99.0 indicates invalid.

Field_Binary.name: vld_ul_stn
Field_Binary.description: Validated uplink station. ; The uplink station per the validation process. A value of 0 means that the antenna is unknown or not valid.

Field_Binary.name: vld_dop_mode
Field_Binary.description: Validated doppler mode. ; 0 => Unknown or not applicable; 1 => One-way; 2 => Two-way; 3 => Three-way

Field_Binary.name: vld_scft_coh
Field_Binary.description: Validated spacecraft coherency. ; 0 => Unknown or not applicable; 1 => Coherent; 2 => Non-coherent; 3 => Transponded, non-coherent

Field_Binary.name: vld_dl_band
Field_Binary.description: Validated downlink frequency band.; 0 => Unknown; 1 => S-band; 2 => X-band; 3 => Ka-band; 4 => Ku-band; 5 => L-band; 6 => S or X band (26m stations)

Field_Binary.name: scft_transpd_lock
Field_Binary.description: Spacecraft transponder lock.; 0 => Unknown; 1 => Out-of-lock; 2 => In Lock

Field_Binary.name: scft_transpd_num
Field_Binary.description: Spacecraft transponder number.; 0 if unknown, transponder number otherwise.

Field_Binary.name: reserve2
Field_Binary.description: Reserved.; Two bytes.

Field_Binary.name: scft_osc_freq
Field_Binary.description: Spacecraft oscillator frequency.; Spacecraft one?way frequency. 0.0 if unknown.

Field_Binary.name: scft_transpd_delay
Field_Binary.description: Spacecraft transponder delay.; Coherent ranging delay. Value of ?1.0 indicates invalid.

Field_Binary.name: scft_transpd_turn_num
Field_Binary.description: Spacecraft transponder turn around ratio numerator.; A value of 0 indicates unknown.

Field_Binary.name: scft_transpd_turn_den
Field_Binary.description: Spacecraft transponder turn around ratio denominator.; A value of 0 indicates unknown.

Field_Binary.name: scft_twnc_stat
Field_Binary.description: Spacecraft two-way non-coherent (TWNC) status.; 0 => Unknown; 1 => OFF; 2 => ON

Field_Binary.name: scft_osc_type
Field_Binary.description: Spacecraft oscillator type.; 0 => Unknown; 1 => AUX OSC (auxiliary oscillator); 2 => USO (ultra-stable oscillator)

Field_Binary.name: mod_day
Field_Binary.description: Modification time days.; Days since 1/1/1958. Last modification time.

Field_Binary.name: mod_msec
Field_Binary.description: Modification time milliseconds of day. ; Last modification time.

Field_Binary.name: cnt_time
Field_Binary.description: Count time.; Integration time of the counts. Value of 0 indicates Not Applicable

Field_Binary.name: version_num
Field_Binary.description: Version number.; Version number of the assembly that generated the data.

Field_Binary.name: sub_version_num
Field_Binary.description: Sub-version number.; Sub-version number of the assembly that generated the data.

Field_Binary.name: sub_sub_version_num
Field_Binary.description: Sub-sub-version number.; Sub-sub-version number of the assembly that generated the data.

Field_Binary.name: lna_corr_value
Field_Binary.description: LNA Correction Value.; Indicates results of validation of LNA number.; Value of 0 indicates no validation or correction was made, otherwise if non-zero, this value is to be used instead of lna_num .

Field_Binary.name: chdo_type
Field_Binary.description: Type attribute of the PN range data CHDO.; CHDO contains binary data.

Field_Binary.name: chdo_length
Field_Binary.description: Length attribute of the PN range data CHDO value field.; Number of bytes after this item.

Field_Binary.name: ul_stn_cal
Field_Binary.description: Uplink station calibration value.; Invalid indicated by value of -1.0.

Field_Binary.name: dl_stn_cal
Field_Binary.description: Downlink station calibration value.; Invalid indicated by value of -1.0.

Field_Binary.name: meas_rng
Field_Binary.description: Measured range value. ; Does not include compensation for station calibration and other adjustments. Invalid is indicated by value of -1.0.

Field_Binary.name: rng_obs_dl
Field_Binary.description: Downlink range observable.; Includes measurement adjustments (station calibration, time tag offsets, spacecraft delay, and Z-height). Invalid is indicated by value of -1.0.

Field_Binary.name: figure_merit
Field_Binary.description: Probability of Acquistion. ; Formerly called Figure of Merit , this is the probability of acquiring the correct range.;

Field_Binary.name: drvid
Field_Binary.description: DRVID.; DRVID measured using doppler data from carrier

Field_Binary.name: rtlt
Field_Binary.description: Round trip light time.; Predicted value.

Field_Binary.name: prn0
Field_Binary.description: Pr/N0.; Ranging power to noise spectral density ratio.

Field_Binary.name: transmit_pwr
Field_Binary.description: Transmitter power.

Field_Binary.name: invert
Field_Binary.description: Invert.; Inverted implies that the polarity of the correlation reference is the invert of what was transmitted.; 0 => Not inverted; 1 => Inverted

Field_Binary.name: correl_type
Field_Binary.description: Correlation type.; 0 => Squarewave; 1 => Sinewave

Field_Binary.name: chip_rate
Field_Binary.description: Chip Rate.; The PN pattern chip rate in Megachips/sec, rounded down. ;

Field_Binary.name: len_subcode1
Field_Binary.description: Subcode #1 length.; A value of 0 implies no subcode.

Field_Binary.name: len_subcode2
Field_Binary.description: Subcode #2 length.; A value of 0 implies no subcode.

Field_Binary.description: Subcode #5 length.; A value of 0 implies no subcode.

Field_Binary.description: Subcode #6 length.; A value of 0 implies no subcode.

Field_Binary.description: Operation #1.; Logical operation between the accumulated pattern and the next subcode.; 0 => AND; 1 => OR; 2 => XOR; 3 => Weighted Vote, weight = 1; 4 => Weighted Vote, weight = 2; 5 => Weighted Vote, weight = 3; 6 => Weighted Vote, weight = 4; 7 => Weighted Vote, weight = 5; 8 => Weighted Vote, weight = 6

Field_Binary.description: Operation #2.; (See Item op_subcode1)

Field_Binary.description: Operation #3.; (See Item op_subcode1)

Field_Binary.description: Subcode #2 component value. ; Definition of the subcode.

Field_Binary.description: Subcode #3 component value. ; Definition of the subcode.

Field_Binary.description: Subcode #4 component value. ; Definition of the subcode.

Field_Binary.description: Subcode #5 component value. ; Definition of the subcode.

Field_Binary.name: def_subcode6
Field_Binary.description: Subcode #6 component value. ; Definition of the subcode.

Field_Binary.name: pn_code_length
Field_Binary.description: PN Code Length.

Field_Binary.name: transmit_inphs_time
Field_Binary.description: Transmit In-phase time.; Offset from time tag of time of zero phase on uplink range signal generation.

Field_Binary.name: rcv_inphs_time
Field_Binary.description: Receive In-phase time.; Offset from time tag of time of zero phase on downlink range signal correlation.

Field_Binary.name: carr_sup_rng _modul
Field_Binary.description: Carrier suppression by ranging modulation.; Reduction in carrier power due to ranging modulation.

Field_Binary.name: exc_scalar_num
Field_Binary.description: Exciter Scalar Numerator.; Numerator of ratio between ranging reference signal anduplink sky frequency.

Field_Binary.name: exc_scalar_den
Field_Binary.description: Exciter Scalar Denominator.; Denominator of ratio between ranging reference signal anduplink sky frequency.

Field_Binary.name: rng_cycle_time
Field_Binary.description: Range cycle time.; Integration time for each PN range point.

Field_Binary.name: rng_modulo
Field_Binary.description: Range modulo value.; Range measurement modulo (ambiguity).

Field_Binary.name: rng_type
Field_Binary.description: Range measurement type.; Type of PN measurement.; 0 => Ranging Round Trip; 1 => Calibration; 2 => Telemetry-Based Ranging; 3 => 1-way to Spacecraft; 4 => 1-way from Spacecraft; 5 => Coupled Noncoherent

Field_Binary.name: fabricated_ul_flag
Field_Binary.description: Fabricated uplink flag.; Indicates whether this SFDU was created based on uplink records fabricated in support of 3-way ranging.; 0 => SFDU created using uplink records originally generated by UPL and validated by TTC software; 1 => SFDU created using uplink records fabricated by TTC software

Field_Binary.name: rng_noise
Field_Binary.description: Range noise.; Invalid indicated by value of -1.0.

Field_Binary.name: rng_dl_prefit_resid
Field_Binary.description: Downlink range pre-fit residual.; Observed range minus predicted range.

Field_Binary.name: rng_dl_prefit_resid_vld_flag
Field_Binary.description: Downlink range pre-fit residual validity indicator.; 0 => Invalid pre-fit residual data; 1 => Valid pre-fit residual data

Field_Binary.name: clock_waveform
Field_Binary.description: Uplink clock waveform type.; 0 => Squarewave; 1 => Sinewave

Field_Binary.name: rng_resid_tol_value
Field_Binary.description: Range residual tolerance value.; Value used for setting Range residual tolerance flag. Provided by customer. Applies to rng_dl_prefit_resid; not applicable if rng_dl_prefit_resid_vld_flag is 0.

Field_Binary.name: drvid_tol_value
Field_Binary.description: DRVID tolerance value.; Value used for setting DRVID tolerance flag. Provided by customer.

Field_Binary.name: prn0_resid_tol_value
Field_Binary.description: Pr/N0 residual tolerance value.; Value used for setting Pr/N0 residual tolerance flag. Provided by customer.

Field_Binary.name: rng_sigma_tol_value
Field_Binary.description: Range sigma tolerance value.; Value used for setting Range sigma tolerance flag. Provided by customer. Not applicable if rng_noise is set to -1.0.

Field_Binary.name: fom_tol_value
Field_Binary.description: Probability of Acquisition tolerance value.; Value used in setting of Range Validity flag. Provided by customer.

Field_Binary.name: rng_resid_tol_flag
Field_Binary.description: Range residual tolerance flag.; Not applicable if rng_dl_prefit_resid_vld_flag is 0.; 0 => Out of tolerance; 1 => In tolerance

Field_Binary.name: drvid_tol_flag
Field_Binary.description: DRVID tolerance flag.; 0 => Out of tolerance; 1 => In tolerance

Field_Binary.name: prn0_resid_tol_flag
Field_Binary.description: Pr/N0 residual tolerance flag.; 0 => Out of tolerance; 1 => In tolerance

Field_Binary.name: rng_sigma_tol_flag
Field_Binary.description: Range sigma tolerance flag.; Not applicable if rng_noise is set to -1.0.; 0 => Out of tolerance; 1 => In tolerance

Field_Binary.name: rng_vld_flag
Field_Binary.description: Range validity flag.; 0 => Invalid; 1 => Valid

Field_Binary.name: rng_config_flag
Field_Binary.description: Range configuration change flag.; 0 => Changed; 1 => Unchanged

Field_Binary.name: stn_cal_corr_flag
Field_Binary.description: Station calibration correction flag.; Indicates results of validation of the station calibration value.; 0 => Unable to correct; 1 => Validated, no change; 2 => Validated, changed uplink; 3 => Validated, changed downlink; 4 => Validated, changed both uplink and downlink

Field_Binary.description: Operation #6.; (See Item op_subcode1); ;
